text: Mikhail Sergeyevich Biryukov (; 28 April 1992 â€“ 4 October 2019) was a Russian junior tennis player. His highest ATP singles ranking was 292. After his retirement from professional tennis at age 22, he was a coach of under 16 player Alexey Zakharov. He was the son of four-time World Champion in modern pentathlon, Irina Kiseleva. He won the silver medal in the inaugural Youth Olympic Games held in Singapore. On 4 October 2019, Biryukov was found dead in Moscow at the age of 27. ==References== Category:1992 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Russian tennis players
